feat(W6-bugfix): re-embed detached window back into Tab (press F6)

Adds the reverse operation of Ctrl+D detach: once a child has been
detached into its own top-level window, the user can press F6 inside
that window to re-embed it as a fresh tab in the original mhtabx
host.

Protocol:
  - common.h: MHX_REMBED_REQUEST = WM_APP + 28
    direction: child -> host
    wp = child_hwnd, lp = 0
    return = new slot_id (>= 0) or -1 on failure

  - IpcProtocol.h: SendReembedRequest helper
    Uses SendMessageTimeoutW (3s) so the child can read the new
    slot_id from the return value and update its local state.

ChildProcessManager::AdoptExternalWindow(HWND, title):
  - GetWindowThreadProcessId maps HWND back to pid.
  - OpenProcess(SYNCHRONIZE | PROCESS_QUERY_LIMITED_INFORMATION)
    retrieves a new hProcess for wait-handle tracking. If OpenProcess
    fails (rare, e.g. elevation mismatch) we still proceed with
    hProcess=nullptr; the child window can be embedded but exit
    detection will rely on MHX_CLEANUP_VIEW instead of wait handles.
  - Builds a ChildSlot, calls TabController::AddSlot + EmbedChildWindow.
    The existing EmbedChildWindow strips WS_OVERLAPPEDWINDOW and
    applies WS_CHILD|WS_VISIBLE|WS_CLIPSIBLINGS, then SetParent to the
    tab control, so the floating frame disappears automatically.
  - Registers the wait handle last so Poll works if the child exits.

MainFrame::OnRembedRequest:
  - Reads child_hwnd from wp.
  - GetWindowTextW grabs the current caption as a sensible tab title.
  - AdoptExternalWindow + HeartbeatMonitor::RegisterSlot + PostActivateView.
  - Returns new slot_id to the child synchronously.

demo_child.cpp:
  - VK_F6 handler sends MHX_REMBED_REQUEST synchronously, reads the
    new slot_id from the return value, writes it into state.slot_id
    so the rest of the IPC (HIDE_VIEW/ACTIVATE_VIEW/HEARTBEAT) keeps
    working with the right id.
  - PaintBody text updated: 'ESC: cleanup tab' / 'F6: reembed to host'.
